==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Suberic
<hw>Su*ber"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>suber</ets>
the cork tree: cf. F. <ets>sub⟦eacute⟧reque</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>Of or pertaining to cork; specifically,
designating an acid, <chform>C6H12.(CO2H)2</chform>, homologous with
oxalic acid, and obtained from cork and certain fatty oils, as a white
crystalline substance.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Suberin</ent>⟦br⟧
